parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy or deploy improperly.
symptoms: The airbag light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag deploys with excessive force
the airbag causes injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Sensor or Control Unit Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor or control unit can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to unexpected deployments or failures to deploy in a crash.
symptoms: The airbag light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper deployment of airbags can cause serious injuries, including eye injuries, facial injuries, and broken bones.
symptoms: Injuries sustained from airbag deployment
including eye injuries
facial injuries
and broken bones.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to honor airbag recalls can lead to continued risks of airbag system failures and injuries.
symptoms: Dealerships refusing to perform airbag recall repairs
parts not being available for recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine dies or stalls while driving
often without warning
and may restart after a short time. The vehicle may jerk or hesitate before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Distributor failure can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
and the distributor cap or rotor may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical wiring harness failure can cause fires, engine stalling, or loss of power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: White smoke may come from under the vehicle
and the engine may catch fire. The vehicle may stall or lose power
and the electrical system may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to engine stalling or failure to start.
symptoms: The alternator may blow out
causing the battery to drain
and the vehicle may stall or fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent electrical problems can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Interior lights may go out
power windows may malfunction
and the horn may be inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failure can cause the engine to fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The battery may explode or drain
causing the engine to fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission may freeze in park
and the vehicle may need to be towed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuse failure can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Brake lights may fail
and the fuse may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine shakes violently at idling
trembles when applying gas
has difficulty starting
and stalls frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fogged headlights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights are dim or foggy
reducing visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain guide can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The timing chain guide needs to be replaced repeatedly
resulting in high repair costs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leaks from Front Rubber O-Ring or Engine Seals
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded. They can also cause environmental damage and create a fire hazard.
symptoms: Oil stains on the garage floor
oil leaks from the front of the engine
oil leaks from the valve cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause a loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
causing the vehicle to die while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective engine can cause various problems, including oil leaks, antifreeze leaks, and stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents and lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: Oil leaks
antifreeze leaks
smoke under the hood
engine stalling.
